# TypeScript Conventions

- Strict mode always — `"strict": true` in tsconfig
- No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow, or define proper types
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for data shapes; use `interface` only for things that extend
- Export types from co-located files near the feature they serve
- Use Zod for runtime validation at system boundaries (Server Actions, API routes)
- Prefer const assertions and discriminated unions over enums
